page.title: 20Round About Wick
page.content: In a field to the left of the church there was an old mill now used as flats. Nearby there was a natural wood with many different types of trees. This means that it has grown up since the war. Fields of over 100 years old would have been one field are now many smaller meadows. Mr Upward owns all the land around. The fields are used for Wheat, Barley and fruit and nut trees. In the hedgerows there is a rich variety of growth. Nearby is the sewage works and 200 metres away is a mansion called"The Manor House". Also in Wick there are a few factories called Plasticfilm and Runacres.
